TAJBank, Nigeria’s innovative non-interest financial institution has announced its appointment as a receiving agent by the Nigerians Customs Service (NCS). With the appointment, the non-interest bank will be serving as the official agent for the NCS for the collection of all forms of revenues. In a statement issued by the bank, the management restated the lender’s commitment to deploy cutting edge information technology to broaden the revenue collection platforms of the NCS. It assured: “This will be achieved through provision of various e-based options to be made available to revenue payers. This model is expected to ease revenue collection and boost the federal government’s revenue drive. The bank looks forward to fostering a mutually rewarding relationship with the NCS.” Dear valued readers, subscribe to the Daily Trust e-paper to continue enjoying our diet of authoritative news. Kindly subscribe here TAJBank is Nigeria’s second non-interest financial institution, offering an exciting array of products and services that span private banking, retail banking, business banking, development finance and the public sector.  TAJBank announces issuance of N150bn FGN Sukuk Bond TaJBank launches another branch in Kano TAJ Bank hosts non-interest forum for treasurers, others